-- United Engineers shares up after OCBC enters exclusive talks with Thai billionaire on stake sale
-- By Aradhana Aravindan and Rachel Armstrong
-- Tue Aug 26, 2014 09:05PM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, Aug 27 (Reuters) - Shares of United Engineers Ltd <UTES.SI> rose 2.2 percent after Oversea Chinese Banking Corporation <OCBC.SI> and Great Eastern Holdings <GELA.SI> said they are in exclusive talks with a company controlled by Thai billionaire Charoen Sirivadhanabhakdi regarding the sale of the Singapore firms' stake in the engineering and property company.

